@node Introduction "Introduction to IconDT"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}IconDT@{ub} is a @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes} subclass for loading and displaying @{"Amiga Icons" link Icons}. Once installed it will let all @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes} aware programs to recognize and load @{"Amiga Icons" link Icons} as pictures.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements for IconDT"

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}IconDT@{ub} requires AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher (@{i}datatypes.library @{ui}and @{i}icon.library @{ui}V39+).
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation of IconDT"

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

 Use supplied @{i}Installer @{ui}script to copy necessary files. If you go for "Manually Selectable" installation you will need to activate class by double-clicking on @{i}DEVS:DataTypes/Icon @{ui} icon or using @{i}AddDataTypes @{b}REFRESH @{ub}@{ui}from Shell.
@endnode

@node Configuration "Configuring operation of IconDT"

  @{b}@{u}Configuration@{uu}@{ub}

 You can use a config file to customize operation of @{b}IconDT@{ub} and thus appearance of icons on screen. The config file is
  @{i}ENV:DataTypes/icon.prefs @{ui}
 The config file is a multi-line ASCII file. Each line could have one command word. Some Pararmeters will only cause an action on some icon-types. So e.g. only the tool-icon could have a toolwindow.
 If all parameters are set, the standard image will be shown!

@{fg highlight}PARAMETERS@{fg text}
 @{b}NOTUNSELECTED@{ub} - do ot show the unselected (standard) image (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTSELECTED@{ub} - do not show the selected image (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTUNUSED@{ub} - do not show unused entrys (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTTYPE@{ub} - do not show the icon type (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTDEFTOOL@{ub} - do not show the default tool (@{i}disk, project@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTTOOLTYPE@{ub} - do not show the tooltypes (@{i}drawer, project, tool@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTTOOLWINDOW@{ub} - do not show the toolwindow (@{i}tool@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTSTACKSIZE@{ub} - do not show the stacksize (@{i}project, tool@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTDATE@{ub} - do not show the icon-date (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTFLAGS@{ub} - do not show the icon-flags (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTSIZE@{ub} - do not show the icon-size (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTCOMMENT@{ub} - do not show the icon-comment (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}NOTFILENAME@{ub} - do not show the icon-filename (@{i}all@{ui}).
 @{b}FONTNAME=@{ub} - select a font for the output (@{i}all texts@{ui}).
 @{b}FONTSIZE=@{ub} - select the size of the selected font (@{i}all texts@{ui}).

 You could also use DTpref V4.0 or higher (look into the AmiNet for it) for configurating the @{b}IconDT@{ub}. Here you have to set a tooltype in the DTpref-Icon which look like this one:
  @{b}DT=icon.datatype,SYS:disk.info@{ub}
 With DTpref V3.1 or higher you could also use the internal preferences setup of DTpref.
@endnode

