@node DataTypes "DataTypes Information"
@prev DataTypes
@next DataTypes

  @{b}@{u}DataTypes@{uu}@{ub}

 @{i}DataTypes @{ui}is an AmigaDOS subsystem (introduced in AmigaDOS 3.0) for dealing with different types of files found on different machines (PC's, Macs and Amigas). @{i}DataTypes @{ui}can be used to recognize type of any file and to interpret informations stored in that file. A client application such as @{i}MultiView @{ui}can then show that data in an appropriate way.

   @{i}DataTypes @{ui}divide all files into the following main categories:
   À @{i}syst @{ui}(System) - system files;
   À @{i}text @{ui}(Text) - textual files;
   À @{i}docu @{ui}(Document) - documents (spreadsheet data, text with
     pictures etc.);
   À @{i}soun @{ui}(Sound) - sound samples;
   À @{i}inst @{ui}(Instrument) - musical instruments;
   À @{i}musi @{ui}(Music) - songs;
   À @{i}pict @{ui}(Picture) - graphics;
   À @{i}anim @{ui}(Animation) - animations;
   À @{i}movi @{ui}(Movie) - animations with sound.
   Each category is further divided into sub-classes. Each sub-class interprets one type of file, converting it to some universal format.
  @{b}icon.datatype@{ub} is a sub-class of Picture group.
@endnode

